tip.text: GREAT place, nice clientele. Very good craft cocktails, food is really good too. The fried spring rolls (pic) are AMAZING!!
Great food, very reasonable prices. Breakfast sandwich is very good. The famous cinnamon focaccia (pic) is AWESOME, get a coffee with it 😄
The Super Campechana (pic) is AWESOME!! The fish taco (pic) is the BEST I have ever had, vodka oyster shooter is a must. Great food here, good beers on tap.
Great concept of build your own poke bowl. Loved it. Got the 4 scoops with spicy tuna, albacore, tuna and spicy salmon, all were very fresh. The mango habanero sauce is tasty 😋
This 28 seat speakeasy is hidden inside the Downtown Cocktail Room. A real treat, quaint & exclusive. Elite mixologist create tantalizing hand crafted cocktails. Negroni is delicious. Nice clientele.
This dive bar is a REAL gem, BEST live music in Vegas. GREAT hand crafted cocktails, only $10, bartenders are AWESOME! Good beer selection. Pool & shuffle board tables. Great clientele, Clean place.
Good food, nice wines, very friendly staff and bartenders. Live music occasionally.

venue.name: Grape Street Cafe, Wine Bar & Cellar

tip.text: Very authentic, like eating in Mexico. The tacos are AWESOME, both the chicken and beef, only $1.25 each. Grilled chicken is VERY delicious. A hole in the wall but clean. Friendly staff.
VERY crowded, VERY loud. Food is good, Steak Eyes (pic) is tasty, ask for extra gravy. Good coffee, smoothies, waffles. Friendly attentive staff.

formattedAddress: 6261 Dean Martin Dr Ste C29 (Dean Martin and Post)

tip.text: I like this place, very casual, very good bar food etc.. The cheese curds are awesome!! The Black Lab Stout is the BEST beer here. So creamy and smooth, yummy. 👍👍
GREAT food, the Naked Peruvian wrap (pic) is AWESOME!! big enough to share. Green beans are really good, as is the stuffed avocado with chicken. The yellow sauce is very tasty 😋
The food here is GREAT. The Braised Pork Neck Bones (pic) are AMAZING, a MUST!! So tender & the broth is perfectly spiced. Come Monday night for open mic, local artists from the Strip sing, awesome.
The tuna salad (pic) is AMAZING!! Great sandwiches and breakfast too. Daily specials are always really good and the coffee is awesome.

formattedAddress: 3225 S Rainbow Blvd Ste 106 (W Desert Inn Rd)

tip.text: The salsa & guacamole are both VERY good. The crispy dynamite shrimp tacos (pic) are AWESOME!! Order a Negroni with tequila instead of gin, soooo good 😄Friendly staff & bartenders.

VERY classy speakeasy. This private, 20 person cocktail lounge inside the Commonwealth is hands down the best kept secret in Vegas. Every cocktail is personalized & hand crafted to perfection. AMAZING
Great place, open 24 hours, reasonable prices. Pho is AMAZING!! Braised catfish in clay pot (pic) is good, very rich, so get a side of rice with it. Green beans w/pork, & walnut shrimp are GREAT.

formattedAddress: 4029 Spring Mountain Rd (at S. Wynn Rd.)

tip.text: GREAT Saloon/bar neat decor, dollar bills hanging from ceiling. Drinks are awesome, beer is cold. Bison burger, steaks, ribs all amazing. Go to the restroom & piss in a bathtub 😄  peacocks outside.
Very small place, GREAT drinks, especially the Fink Bomb (very strong & yummy). Tiki hut decor, good music, friendly bartenders. Good place to start or end the night.
Some of the best cocktails in Vegas. Great bar tenders, decent prices. Live music with bands on the back patio on occasion. Great cocktail lounge where you can have a conversation & meet people.
Beautifully decorated hotel, lounge, restaurant. Definitely worth coming here for food or drinks to see it. Love all the art on the ceilings, & old furniture. Great drinks and live music at the bar.
The roof top bar here is AWESOME!! Great live music, hookah / shisha, good view looking down on east Fremont street. Friendly staff & good drinks.
Good place to grab a slice of pizza & a beer late at night in between crawling the bars on east Fremont. Whole pies as well. The white cheese pizza is very good. Patio out back, god music.
Really neat bar, great interior with the old brick look, fire pits, and good seating areas. Music was too loud the night we were there. Good drinks, bar tenders are super friendly.

formattedAddress: 511 Fremont St (at S Las Vegas Blvd)

tip.text: Good food truck, GREAT brisket sliders and nice cold beer. They also have chicken and beef sliders. It was at the south terminal of the Austin airport when I ate there.
The grinders here are AWESOME!! The pizza is good too. Reasonably priced and good service.
Beautiful marina, great place to walk around and shop, rent a boat etc.. Great restaurants and a few bars as well.

formattedAddress: 34624 Golden Lantern Dr. (Dana Point Harbor Drive)

tip.text: Chicken is VERY good here, ribs are tasty too. Great choice of sides, all pretty good. Great meal for the price, and fast service.
The grits are AWESOME!! Quail was ok, a little slow on service and the music SUCKS and was too loud, took away from the dinning experience.
The crab is a MUST, squid, and Oysters are really good to, nice cold beer. Sit next to the ocean, the waves are awesome.
Good resort, nice rooms, the staff is very friendly and attentive. Grounds are beautiful, loved the outdoor fire pit and outdoor seating at the Red Bar. Food is good.
Great bartenders they make great drinks. Outdoor seating and fire pit is awesome. Good bar food. Nice clientele.
Good food on the breakfast buffet as well as off the menus. Great bottomless cup of coffee. Sit outside overlooking the golf course and grounds, it's very nice. GREAT wait staff.
AWESOME Hookah lounge. Lot's of brands of shisha, tons of flavors. LARGE hookahs that pull very well. Great service, very nice decor, cold beer, wine, full bar, bar food.
One of my favorite places in Sydney. You have to try the kangaroo pizza, it is great. So is the crocodile. The beer selection here is AWESOME!! Lots of unique beers.
One of the BEST kept secrets in Vegas. The food is AMAZING!! 50 wines, under $50. Drunken noodles duck (pic) is a MUST. Grilled prawns, fried prawns, calamari are awesome.

venue.name: Chada Street Thai Restaurant & Wine Bar

tip.text: The oldest bar in Southern Nevada, over 100 yrs old. Was actually purchased through a Sears catalog. Great landmark of old old west. Featured in movies & TV shows. Check the walls for bullet holes.
This is the salon Clark Gable drank & spent 3 days in while awaiting word of the death of his wife, Carol Lombard, whose plane crashed into nearby mountain in 1942. Great history here, lots to see.
FANTASTIC, dive bar, 50's, retro, antique store all in one. Great music, sometimes live, good draft beers on tap, very reasonable prices. Outdoor patio in the back. 👍👍

Cute, charming little place. Egg au gratin with bacon (pic) is VERY good, as was is the coffee. A weird, cold vibe. Unhelpful wait staff, they act like they are doing you a favor wait on you. Very odd
Great place, friendly staff. Get the Truffle Boschetto cheese with black & white truffle pieces, pair it with the "If You See Kay Red Blend" wine & you will have mouthgasam. Out of this world combo ❤

Neat little dive bar, pool table, dart board, gaming machines on the bar. GREAT music. Apocalypse IPA on tap is awesome!! Chicken strips VERY good, hand breaded in the kitchen. Lot's of flats screens.
Great cocktail bar, lively & crowded on the weekends with a DJ. Quieter during the week.  Nice place to grab a drink, meet other locals & tourist alike. Great martinis, very friendly waitresses.

location.crossStreet: at Red Rock Casino Resort Spa
formattedAddress: 11011 W Charleston Blvd (at Red Rock Casino Resort Spa)

tip.text: The BEST Thai food in Vegas. The Hot Basil Beef (pic) is awesome, so many amazing spices & flavors exploding in your mouth at the same time, WOW!! Coconut & green tea ice cream (pic) is so so good 😋
The braised lamb shank (pic) is marinated for hours, and seasoned to perfection, a MUST!! Soooo good.
Great place, friendly staff, small outside patio with 4 or 5 tables. Many types of hummus, the hot pita bread (pic) fresh out of the oven is amazing. The jalapeño hummus (pic) is AWESOME!!
Really neat, speakeasy type place, very relaxed vibe & friendly bar tenders. GREAT drinks, love the ones with the large round ice cube (pic).
REALLY GOOD coffee here, good blueberry muffins (pic) too. Nice place to relax, work on your computer, read a book etc.. Very friendly staff.
VERY nice Thai restaurant. Pineapple curry is a MUST! I have traveled the world, it is some of the best curry I ever had. Tum Yum soup is REALLY good, & the coconut ice cream is amazing, so yummy 😋❤️
GREAT Thai food, the seafood salad (pic) is AWESOME!! It's LOADED with lots of delicious seafood, great as a meal or big enough to share prior to the meal. The service is fast & the staff is friendly
Back again for an AWESOME shine, love how they use the torch (pic) to heat the wax, leaves a deep, luxurious glow, BEST shine you will ever get.

formattedAddress: Concourse D, Outisde US Airways Club (CLT Airport)
location.address: Concourse D, Outisde US Airways Club

tip.text: Love the roof top bar here, GREAT VIEW of the city. Good nachos & wings. Pretty good selection of scotch, about a dozen beers on tap. Good brunch too.
By far the BEST brewery in Charlotte, & one of the few that actually serve food. The Maple Canyon (pic) is AMAZING!! Great staff, nice patio.
Great movie theater, & reclining seats. Good food, snacks, drinks and alcohol beverages delivered to you before / during the movie. The Nutella filled beignets (pic) are a MUST!! so delicious 😋

formattedAddress: 210 E Trade St (at S College St)

tip.text: The shrimp Tum Yum soup (pic) is a must, lots of great flavors, AMAZING!! Great curries here too.
Great sports bar, wide screens, cold beer and good drinks. Very friendly staff. The pepperoni rolls (pic) are awesome, the homemade potato chips (pic) are very good 😄❤️

formattedAddress: 230 E W T Harris Blvd (N Tryon)

tip.text: Crab & shrimp dip (pic) is AWESOME!! Good wings, and beer. Staff was friendly and attentive. Outdoor seating.
The Jack Frost Punch (pic) is an AMAZINGLY delicious drink. The chocolate bread pudding, with ice cream & carmel is A MUST!! Soooo yummy. Very crowded place, long wait, not for the impatient.
Jalapeño cheese dip (pic) is great. Honey butter croissants,are to die for, house salad with hot bacon house dressing is A MUST!! Ribs, prime rib, sirloin steak all amazing & cooked to perfection ❤️👍
GREAT place for wine & cocktails, very nice clientele & atmosphere. Small, crowded, hard to get a table. Garlic shrimp is good, lamb lollipops are AMAZING, a MUST, so flavorful, cooked to perfection.

Great little hookah bar, very authentic. Nice variety of shisha flavors, 3 brands, Al Fakher, Starbuzz, & Nakhla. GREAT Turkish Coffee. No alcohol or food, but snacks, desserts, soft drinks, tea etc..
This place is GREAT, the service is awesome, the staff is very friendly. The steak is incredible, cooked to perfection. The salmon BLT, shrimp grits & Hef wings are really good. Great cocktails.
AWESOME dive bar, GREAT live music, good place to meet people, couple of pool tables & dartboard in the back. Beer, wine, liquor etc.. I was here for the 9th anniversary, great cake (pic) & FUN!! 😄
The "Tot"chos are great and the Brown Begged Bacon Crisp are AWESOME!! They taste sooooo good with beer, a MUST!!
Not enough seating, boring atmosphere, no decor. Beers are decent, the red and the Abbey are good. I recommend the flight (pic)
The Korean slider (pic) with kim chi is AWESOME!! The pork belly taco is VERY good (pic).
Best hotdogs around, get'em all the way. Great onion rings, burgers, fries and daily specials. GREAT breakfast, coffee and banana pudding ❤️❤️
Hands down the BEST shoe shine I've ever had, only $5. So worth it. They make your shoes shine like new money. Located on the right as you start down the corridor to D & E gates.

formattedAddress: Concourse D, Outisde US Airways Club (CLT Airport)
location.address: Concourse D, Outisde US Airways Club

tip.text: GREAT sushi burritos. For freshest, most profound taste get them with NO rice. The High Maintenance & Kimchee Beef (not on the menu) with seaweed wrap (no rice) are both AMAZING ❤️
Neat place, 40 - 50 craft beers on tap, mostly local / regional. Pantyhose Porter is very GOOD. I love the large can format, it's nice grab two or three different ones to keep in the fridge at home
Great place for Brunch, lunch or dinner. My steak of choice is the filet here. Crab legs are also good. Great salads as well. Good martinis and wine. Nice place, good clientele.

formattedAddress: 3131 Las Vegas Blvd S (in Wynn Las Vegas)

tip.text: Back again 😄 The bruschetta bar (pic) is to die for, A MUST!! The lasagna was great, as well as the bread pudding, a coupe of nice red wines also.

formattedAddress: 3200 Las Vegas Blvd S (at Fashion Show Mall)

tip.text: Opened in 1955, western decor, not fancy but good food. Steaks and prime rib are really good, so are the burgers. About 15 mins from the Strip, worth it if you are looking for an old west experience
Great steaks, seafood, and wines. Love the salad made table side. Ladies get a complimentary rose 🌹 Nice bar for a glass of wine, great martinis. Very nostalgic, old Vegas.
Really neat, little place, love the decor & relaxing seating areas. Some really good beers on tap, great staff, good food. The brunch biscuits & gravy (pic) are awesome. 5 widescreens behind the bar.
Back again, always GOOD 😊 Fresh Mexican food and GREAT margaritas. Shrimp and cheese quesadilla (pic) are delish. The enchiladas and fajitas are really good too.
Exquisite luxury, all suite, all inclusive golf resort. GREAT restaurants & bars. Very nice spa, gym, tennis courts, one of the largest pools in Central America. BEAUTIFUL white sandy beach.

venue.name: The Westin Golf Resort & Spa, Playa Conchal

tip.text: Exquisite luxury, all suite, all inclusive golf resort. GREAT restaurants & bars. Very nice spa, gym, tennis courts, one of the largest pools in Central America. BEAUTIFUL white sand beach.
This is place is a Visual FEAST. I highly recommend it. The staff is friendly the food is good. The Nutella Bomb desert is a MUST!!
Great hotel & spa, on the bay. Nice large pool & nice pool bar. Good restaurant on the balcony. Rooms are very clean and spacious. Walking distance to shopping and restaurants.

contact.facebookName: Doubletree by Hilton Dar es Salaam - Oysterbay

venue.name: Doubletree by Hilton Dar es Salaam - Oysterbay

tip.text: Really neat place with nice clientele. Small, somewhat cozy. Easy to meet people & strike up conversations. Can be crowded & dancing depending on when you go. Serving wine, beer, drinks & good music.
Small, non fancy place, good food. The Jazz Fries 🍟 (pic) are the BEST thing on the menu, a MUST!! The Karai spicy burger (pic) is GOOD so is the Buta. Several good local beers 🍻👍👍
One of the BEST burgers I've had in a while, the Manly Burger (pic) was INCREDIBLE!! cooked to perfection. Washed it down with an Alagash White beer (pic). So yummy 😄😍❤️
Not a fancy place but decent food. The chicken Tika masala is some of the best I have ever had. The shrimp tandoori (pic) is good but not a lot of flavor. Nice staff, no alcohol 😪
LOVE this place, coffee is always incredibly good and the sweets ROCK!! The cheesecake (pic) is perfect, not to sweet or filling, just delicious 😄
Good as always. The red velvet waffles & chicken (pic) are AWESOME!! The chimichurri steak is VERY good and the homemade sangria is a MUST!! 😍❤️
First time here was decent. This time 👎 they tired to upsell me the executive lounge level for $165 usd more. A ripoff. Old room, carpet appears 20 yrs old, bathroom tile is disgusting  👎👎
Nice place with AF brand shisha, the double apple mint is awesome!! The hookahs pull very well. The Temstout is a nice beer. Good music, friendly, attentive staff. 👍👍
LOVE this place, great atmosphere & music. Authentic Cuban feel & decor, nice vibe during the week. The food is AMAZING ❤️❤️ Get the stuffed butterfly fillet steak (pic) it is soooo good. Inexpensive
The food here is just ok, the meats are over cooked & dry, the lamb was terrible, the service was VERY SLOW. Nothing exotic here unless you consider rabbit &!bull testicles exotic. Won't be black :(
Good coffee shop with some nice specialty coffees and juices. Friendly staff 😄
Very nice restaurant with amazing views and delicious food. Sashimi platter, chicken curry, wage beef & tuna are all INCREDIBLE. Island night on Wed. with great buffet, live music & island dancers. 👍
The BEST restaurant on Aitutaki. Cute, & romantic in the front deck & yard (Sandy floor) of the owners home. The signature dish of tuna stuffed with shrimp & cheese, and the mud crab is a MUST!! ❤️😍
The BEST on Aitutaki. Multi award winning 5 Star resort. 27 luxury  bungalows, impeccably designed, situated directly on the white sand & surrounded by stunning turquoise water. GREAT food and wines
The Sicilian "Mob Boss"(pic) is AWESOME!! Very fresh ingredients & cooked to perfection, feeds 4 - 5 people. Meatballs are a great. Some really nice, unique beers on tap, the porter is VERY good. 😍❤️
Shot the Smith & Wesson 500 (pic) the most powerful production handgun in the world. It's a BLAST!! Ammo is expensive ($55 for 20 rounds) but so worth it. Suggestion: spit the rounds w/ 2 -3 people 👍
Neat hookah lounge, small. $10 per person, all you can smoke. Limited shisha brands, Starbuzz, Fumari, some KM. NO AF or Tangiers 😂 NO alcohol. KM Cactus Lime was AWESOME!! Great staff.
Scallops were awesome, by far the best thing on the menu. Brick oven chicken was good.
A MUST!! One of my favorite areas in Paris. Love the street musicians, lot's of shops, little pubs, restaurants, street magicians, people watching. The little crepe shops are AWESOME, delicious 😄
Awesome selection of beers on draft. Big Dog Peach IPA, the Peanut Butter Stout were amazing. The tempura artichoke (pic) is a MUST!! The Ruben egg rolls, & tempura onion rings (pic) were awesome!!
Great martinis, very good food / appetizers )pic) good atmosphere, music can be very loud depending where you sit. The outside patio is great. TERRIBLE hookah / shisha a rip off, don't buy it.

formattedAddress: 6593 Las Vegas Blvd S (at W Sunset Rd)

tip.text: The empanadas are AMAZING!! The BEST chimichurri ever, you can buy it by the jar and take it home as well. The meat is really good. Get one of the barbecues of various meats.
VERY GOOD pizza. The pepperoni, mushrooms, black olives, thin crush pizza (pic) is AWESOME!! Fried mushrooms were great. Not a big fancy place but friendly staff, that makes great pizza. No alcohol
Very nice, fresh healthy salads, sandwiches, entrees, desserts. The ribeye steak salad (pic) is AWESOME!! Friendly staff.
This place is AWESOME!! If you like beer it is a MUST in SD. Over 40 selections of THEIR OWN brews. The mango, peach, & habanero are incredible!! Some very nice porters, stouts, the IPAs incredible.
AWESOME Authentic Thai food. The Tom Yum Soup, Pineapple Fried Rice, Hot Basil Beef, BK Bay Ribs & the Fried Banana Coconut Ice Cream desert are all a MUST 😄👍 Pretty much everything is good here.
Very FRESH & delicious pizza by the slice. Great pairings of (mostly organic) ingredients make some the best pizza you will ever eat. LOVED the Spice Me Up & the Lasagna slices. Great salads too.
Nice, clean place, good clientele. The art hookah with pineapple bowl and watermelon mint Shisha (pic) is very good.
Great daily caught fish specials. The Ranchero Snapper (pic) with avocado jalapeño sauce is AMAZING!! The slaw with pineapple dressing (pic) is a MUST! Ask for a seat next to the window / GREAT view.
Decent place, with a Mediterranean foods, Falafel, Gyros, kebabs, Shawarma, Baklava etc.. No alcohol. The lemon chicken  & spinach (pic) chicken were pretty good. Good prices.
BEST watering hole in Utah. An old rustic cabin, fireplace inside, fire pit outside, live music occasionally. Bar food or order from the Foundry Grill. Kettle fires are Awesome! GREAT Moscow Mule 👍
VERY nice place, GOOD Mexican food & Margaritas. GREAT Happy Hour. The Poblano shrimp & the grilled jalapeños (pic) are a MUST! Nachos (pic) are BIG & really good for just $5. Friendly staff. 👍👍

VERY GOOD authentic Indian food. The chicken & shrimp tikka masala are both AMAZING!! The shrimp coconut korma is wonderful & both the chicken and shrimp tandoori are awesome! GREAT naan, & cold beer.
Nice, clean restaurant & bar overlooking Callville Bay. Full bar, 6 beers on tap. Pool table, juke box, live music occasionally, dance floor. Good breakfast, biscuits & gravy, burgers, wings, fries
AMAING FOOD HERE!! Ceviche is the BEST in Vegas hands down, chicken poblano enchiladas are to die for, both are MUST!!! Beyond these get the guacamole, watermelon margarita & their decadent deserts.
Decent place, way OVER PRICED for what they offer / serve. Steaks are good NOT great compared to other steak houses in Vegas. Service is hit or miss. Over priced wine list. Good atmosphere.
BEST Mexican food in Vegas. A little pricy, but so worth it for the high quality & unique dishes. The seafood enchiladas are AWESOME!! Jalapeño margarita is a MUST!  Check out theTequila Tree (pic)

formattedAddress: 3730 Las Vegas Blvd S (at Aria Resort & Casino)

tip.text: Really nice hotel in an old castle with a lot of charm & ambiance. Rooms are very nice, views and pool are awesome. Great clientele, great somewhat quite, higher end hotel to relax.
Ok at best, the meats lack seasoning and are pretty bland. Wait staff is marginal, not rude but certainly not overly helpful.
Good lunch buffet, the curry chicken is AWESOME, spiced very well. The chicken masala and tandoori chicken were both good as was the garlic naan. Very friendly and professional staff, inexpensive. 😄
Good place. Pork belly and pork cheek are a MUST. Fried oysters are great. The grilled squid (pic) is awesome!! Nice pleasant wait staff.

formattedAddress: 6555 S Jones Blvd (btwn Sunset Rd. & I-215)

tip.text: Beautiful resort, really liked the pools and beach. GOOD food, and service. Great place.

venue.name: El San Juan Hotel - Curio a Collection by Hilton®

tip.text: Not a whole lot to see other than the bronze Charging Bull (pic). Great place for a photo opp. The bull is 16 feet long and weights 7,000 pounds.
Great to experience as often as you can. So much to do and see. Great music, people watching, and walking in nature. Be sure to do a carriage ride, very relaxing, educational & scenic.

formattedAddress: 59th St to 110th St (5th Ave to Central Park West)

tip.text: Members Only Club. If you have a boat I HIGHLY recommend it. Very  reasonable price & tons of FUN! Monthly events, many on the beach, Margarita Blend Off, Hawaiian Luau, Lobster Party  etc..
LOVE this place, EVERYTHING is awesome! If you like southern style country food, this is as good as it gets. I come here every time I get to Atlanta. The hardest part is deciding what not to order 😄
GOOD food here, GREAT sandwiches, soups, & salads. Very good place for lunch, however very busy. Don't let the crowd stop you from enjoying this great food.
Pretty much everything is good here. The shrimp grits are AMAZING!! The she crab soup is a MUST, the collard greens are GREAT! The bread is awesome, so is the snapper. Great staff. Go hungry 😄

formattedAddress: 1200 Lincoln St (btwn Lady St. & Gervais St.)

tip.text: LOVE this place ❤️ The honey butter    Croissants are decadent. The California Dreaming Salad & w/ house dressing is a MUST (with extra croissants)😄 Potato soup is awesome. Cheese cake is AMAZING!!
Nice, clean place, friendly staff, cold beer. The Rustica pizza & garlic parmesan chicken wings (pic) are GOOD!! Very fresh ingredients on the pizza. They also take Bitcoin for payment 👍👍
GREAT place for drinks, in an actual cave. VERY UNIQUE, very small but you definitely come here if you are in the area. Good alcohol selection, good bartender. 👍👍
VERY beautiful beach. Great for sun bathing, swimming, people watching & relaxing. Plenty of venders to get / or bring you drinks & food. Wildlife all around, birds, monkeys etc..
LOVED this place, HIGHLY recommend it. Big beautiful suites, had a private pool on balcony. Sloffs, monkeys, birds in the trees outside your window / balcony. Awesome spa / massage, great food, wine.
LOVE this place. The chocolate, banana milk shake is a MUST, it's to die for. GREAT banana & macadamia nut pancakes. The salads are fresh and delicious. The coffee is the BEST!!

location.address: On the road to Manuel Antonio Ntl. Park
formattedAddress: On the road to Manuel Antonio Ntl. Park

tip.text: Beautiful scenic lake, clear water. Great for boating, skiing, all types of water sports & fishing. Formed by the Hoover Dam, Lake Mead is 532 ft deep, 112 miles long, and has 759 miles of shoreline
VERY good BBQ and soul / southern food. The 3 meat combo (pic) with baby back ribs, spare ribs, pulled pork is AWESOME!! Collard green, & fried okra are a MUST, and the banana pudding is to die for 😄
Nice place to have a drink and watch the sunset. Good food too.
VERY beautiful cathedral, great place to spend a couple of hours meandering around the outside, good photo opportunities. I recommend visiting the inside as well, equally as beautiful.

venue.name: La Seu | Cathedral of Palma (La Seu | Catedral de Mallorca)

tip.text: Beautiful scenic lake, clear water. Great for boating, skiing, all types of water sports & fishing. Formed by the Hoover Dam, Lake Mead is 532 ft deep, 112 miles long, and has 759 miles of shoreline.
The cakes and cup cakes here are sooooooooooo GOOD!! The frosting is the best anywhere. I highly recommend the red velvet and the chocolate chip.
Most famous street in Singapore, GREAT shopping, all the top brands & designers here. Lot's of good places to eat, hotels, wonderful for walking, browsing, people watching etc.. Great for everyone 😄
GREAT Indian food, nice favors & spices. Shrimp & chicken Tika are awesome, get the one with the pineapple curry. Garlic naan was delicious. Staff was friendly, knowledgable, & service was prompt. 👍
Great coffee shop. The Corn, green chili, bacon quiche (pic) is AWESOME!! Good sandwiches, muffins, cinnamon rolls & bread pudding. Ethiopian Yirgacheffe coffee is the BEST!! Great view outside patio
NOT authentic Mexico food, 90% of dishes are sweetened w/ honey, sugar etc.. even the salsa, too sweet. Chicken enchiladas are good. Queso was cold & too salty, sent I back. No alcohol or tea served.
The BEST Italian ever. Valter is amazing, ask him to design a meal for you, you'll be glad you did. The lemon angel hair is to die for. EVERYTHING is GOOD here. Best restaurant in Salt Lake City.
Good place, went to the shooting range, got the 9mm special, shot 4 different pistols then the bigger riffles. Have fun 😄👍
The BEST $ BIGGEST shisha selection in Vegas. They carry ALL of the top brands including hard to find Tangiers flavors Lots of hookahs, coals, hoses etc.. VERY knowledgeable, friendly staff.
Awesome tacos, the carne asada is probably the BEST I have ever had ❤️❤️❤️ Get the al pastor as well, VERY good 😋
Large place, live music after 9:30. Pool table room, pretty good food & service. Good hookahs, lots of shisha flavors, the downside is they only sale ONE brand (Cuzzins) 😟 sad to be so limited 😱
Great drinks, the Dole Cream with the rum float (pic) is AWESOME!! Good old music, friendly wait staff, nice place to chill with friends or meet new one. Great tiki bar decor.
Really GOOD Sports Bar, lots of wide screens, pool table, dart board, foosball, golf game, karaoke nights, live music nights, full bar & GREAT Food!! Pizzas are AMAZING, so are the burgers & wings.
GREAT sight seeing stop. This is a floating fishing village of people who live on their boats. Grab a boat & guide & have them drive you around it. This is AWESOME!!
GREAT as always. Love the deep dish BJ's Favorite, and the monkey bread dessert 😄 The PM Porter is the best beer on tap - 2016 Gold World Beer Cup℠ award-winning dark ale. AWESOME!! ❤️❤️❤️
Really neat place with a hippy vibe. The hookah pipes were ok, not great, didn't pull very well. A decent selection of shisha flavors. The AF, double apple mint was AWESOME!! Good music & cold beer.
GREAT place, beautiful bartenders in bikinis making incredible cocktails. Awesome, friendly service. 20 different beers, pool tables, wide screens full of sports, nice clientele, REALLY FUN place 😄
The Tom Yum soup (pic) with shrimp was good. The Thai Catfish (pic) was AWESOME!! 😄 Small place, fairly quite, good service.
Nice clean place, decent food. Had the Xiao Long Boa they were good not great. Service was fast and staff was friendly.
Really nice place to chill while waiting on your plane. The wine samplers / flights are very good and reasonably priced. Good small plate type of food  that go well with wine 👍
Nice place, GREAT waterfront view with all the yachts, really good clientele. Nice wines, good food. I really recommend this place for a nice relaxing meal / drinks & possibly meet some trendy people
VERY nice hotel, decor & ambiance. The wait staff are polite however service is EXTREMELY SLOW & disorganized. Very disappointing considering the price & quality of such a high end property.
GREAT place ❤️ Got the Bacon Treo, with scrambled eggs instead of poached, & a side of hollandaise (pic) OMG!! It was AWESOME!! Great, friendly staff & GOOD coffee 😄
VERY good burgers, loved the Fuhgeddaboudit extra hot 😄 The wings (pic) are awesome too. Very fast service and friendly staff. Ice cold beer.
Good seafood, nice selection of fresh fish. The bouillabaisse (pic) is really good. Nice wines and deserts  too 😄
Good steaks and seafood and wine. The grilled octopus salad (pic) is awesome!!
Great place. The hookahs are awesome, good shisha selection. The watermelon mint and the apple mint are very good. Get the Turkish coffee, some of the best I've ever had 😄❤️
GREAT food, oysters were very fresh & delicious, salt & pepper calamari was awesome, the grilled prawns are a MUST. Reasonable prices, good atmosphere, great friendly staff.
INCREDIBLE!! The most delicious hot chocolate on the planet. It's like drink hot liquid chocolate bars, thick, yet not to heavy and yummy. Great deserts too. This place is a MUST!! Don't miss it.
Beautiful beach, lots to do, jet ski, parasail, plenty of places to get cold drinks & food. One side is totally nude the other not. Great water & sun bathing on both side 😄👍
Great bar, good Live Music ❤️ get a bucket of ice cold beer & chill while watching the planes come in 👍 Food is pretty good, the fries are AWESOME!!
This is an AWESOME beach, so much fun, partying & people watching 😄 Go grab the fence when the jets take off, very exhilarating ❤️ Nice cold beer, music & food at the bars at each end of the beach.
Nice place, middle eastern decor,  couple of flat screens with games / sports on them. Good music. GREAT, friendly service. AF & Starbuzz shisha brands, hookah pipes pull good. No alcohol.
AWESOME Ice cream ❤️❤️❤️ get a cone and stroll down Las Olas Blvd. Great fudge and caramel apples as well. So many yummy goodies in this place, somethings for everyone 😄👍

formattedAddress: 809 E Las Olas Blvd (at SE 8th St)

tip.text: VERY good food. The chicken and waffles are AWESOME!! (pic) ❤️❤️❤️ A MUST!! The tuna tartare is really good too 👍 Very crowded but worth it. Great staff, very attentive & nice clientele 😄
Good hookah lounge, cigar & sports bar all in one. Full bar, lots of flat screens to watch games. Hookahs pulled well & a decent shisha selection. The watermelon / mint with a pineapple bowl (pic) ❤️
AMAZING Crab Benedict (pic) ❤️❤️❤️ it's not in the menu so ask them to make it for you, absolutely delicious. The crepes are incredible as well, and really good coffee 😄
The food here is so amazing!! Great atmosphere! It gets crowded so get their early or enjoy a delicious mojito at the bar while you wait. The Scollops are the best thing in the menu they're a MUST!!
GREAT place, AWESOME, (and cheap) Bloody Mary's, mimosa 😄❤️ sit outside & people watch, listen to the live music, good food too
GREAT view, good place to shop and pick up gifts, t-shirts etc.... Ice cold beer and very good cocktails 😄

venue.name: Mtn. Top Home Of The Banana Daiquiri

tip.text: Beautiful white sand beach, and aqua blue water. Plenty of restaurants, cold tropical cocktails & beer. Nice place to snorkel 👍
Great, FUN place, AWESOME CRAFT BEER!! 👍❤️ Get the stout, it is amazing!! 😄 Very friendly staff.
FRICK'N AWESOME!! Best crabs I have ever had. Get the crab sampler for two, it's AMAZING!! The garlic crabs are to die for 👍 Key West shrimp is VERY good. Get the cornbread too, very yummy 😄❤️
Lot's of fun, great food & restaurants, drinks, & people watching 😄 world's largest TV overhead, 2 blocks long, with a zip line ride under it. FREE LIVE MUSIC, & street entertainers. A MUST SEE 👍👍

location.crossStreet: btwn N Main St & Las Vegas Blvd
formattedAddress: 425 Fremont St (btwn N Main St & Las Vegas Blvd)

tip.text: Great place, very lively, good drinks nice beer selections, friendly staff with prompt service. Nice hip, clientele. Great food options.
VERY GOOD place, great atmosphere, very hip / chic clientele. Food is amazing, especially the bison burger, scallops, octopus, & grits 😄 incredible, provocative Art throughout, GREAT drinks ❤️❤️❤️

contact.facebookName: Four Seasons Hotel Silicon Valley at East Palo Alto

venue.name: Four Seasons Resort and Residences Jackson Hole

tip.text: GREAT resort, VERY good food and amazing, unique drinks 🍹😋 very tasty. World class treatment from the staff. Great spa, hot tubs, lounge. Top shelf all the way 👍

contact.facebookName: Four Seasons Hotel Silicon Valley at East Palo Alto

venue.name: Four Seasons Resort and Residences Jackson Hole

tip.text: AWESOME place, a MUST if you like Scotch, whiskey etc. Adam the owner is amazing & VERY knowledgeable. Get a group together & do a tasting or come by yourself. IT'S GREAT 😄❤️
Hands down THE BEST, most authentic Indian food in Vegas. The curries & spices are incredible. Shrimp & chicken tandoori & tikka masala, are to die for. Garlic & onion naan is delish. 😄❤️❤️❤️
GOOD food, Brussel sprouts & buffalo onion rings are AWESOME apps. Ribs (full rack pictured) are awesome, the slaw/salad & cornbread they come with are INCREDIBLE!! ❤️❤️❤️
Great Lamb and chicken Shawarma, hummus and salads. All very nicely flavored. GOOD food.
Great Peruvian food. BY far the BEST ceviche  I have found in Vegas. Get the 3 flavors of ceviche (pic) all are full of fish, shrimp, mussels, octopus, & calamari, VERY GOOD!! ❤️😄
Great place, wonderful Pastries, the chocolate eclair (pic) is INCREDIBLE!! Coffee is really good as well as the crepes and quiche.
Back again for their awesome coffee & another delicious Red Velvet Crepe Cake, sooooooo delicious ❤️😄 LOVE THIS PLACE!! Got the Honey Toast with Nutella, bananas, and vanilla ice cream also, AMAZING!
GREAT Hookahs, & shisha, VERY GOOD, friendly, attentive staff 👍 Hands down the BEST Mediterranean food in Vegas, seasoned & cooked to perfection. The Layla's Mixed Grill (pic) AWESOME!! ❤️😄
GREAT Coffee & desserts ❤️😄 THE red velvet crepe cake (pic) it is DELICIOUS, somewhat lite & not too sweet. TIP: get it with chocolate sauce instead of the raspberry it comes with, SO YUMMY 👍

GREAT place, friendly staff, quick service, cool, quaint interior. The caprese salad (pic) is AMAZING, fresh & delicious. Really GOOD coffee too. Fantastic lunch spot, outdoor seating / patio as well.

formattedAddress: 3225 S Rainbow Blvd Ste 106 (W Desert Inn Rd)

tip.text: Nice place, friendly staff. Coffee rewards cards earns you FREE coffee. Get the organic Ethiopian, take a bag home, YUMMY. Apple muffins are AWESOME, so moist & delicious 😄❤️
Get the Root Beer Float Hookah with ice cream in the base. It is AWESOME!! Also the Chocolate Mint with Bananas Fosters, very good. Great place, good staff.
Their house beers are AWESOME, they have lots of constantly change guest beer that are great too. Their seasonal beer, The Dutch (Belgian Tripel) is AMAZING, ❤️ the BEST!! Get a growler to go 👍😄

formattedAddress: 831 W Bonanza Rd (N Martin Luther King Blvd)
